org.bytedeco.javacpp

Class opencv_core.FileNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.bytedeco.javacpp.Pointer
      • org.bytedeco.javacpp.opencv_core.FileNode
  • Enclosing class:
    opencv_core

    public static class opencv_core.FileNode
extends Pointer
    File Storage Node class The node is used to store each and every element of the file storage opened for reading - from the primitive objects, such as numbers and text strings, to the complex nodes: sequences, mappings and the registered objects. Note that file nodes are only used for navigating file storages opened for reading. When a file storage is opened for writing, no data is stored in memory after it is written.
